						<summary>

						<p>On the Nandi pillar of the Pāṭaḷa-Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>[Dēvarāya I], A.D. 1413 (?)</p>						

						<p>Dated Śaka 1343, <hi rend="italic">Vijaya, Mārgaśira,</hi> śu. 11, Sunday, (Irregular). If the cyclic year is true, it corresponds to Ś. 1335 and the details tally for A.D. 1413, December 3.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Refers to some gift for the merit of the king (name lost).</p>						

